      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__THREADS_1ga533a299d4f2ce0d8f3413547f60d00af" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>PIN_DEPRECATED_API <ref refid="group__THREADS_1ga6fde44fe8696d51b99500e26aa0e4c61" kindref="member">PIN_THREAD_UID</ref></type>
        <definition>PIN_DEPRECATED_API PIN_THREAD_UID PIN_ThreadUid</definition>
        <argsstring>()</argsstring>
        <name>PIN_ThreadUid</name>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Get unique identifier of the current thread in Pin. <simplesect kind="return"><para>Unique ID of the current thread in Pin or INVALID_PIN_THREAD_UID upon failure.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Tool writers should not try and use the returned ID to wait for a thread using <ref refid="group__THREADS_1gaddd0dc2709292f807cb233e5ec0f809a" kindref="member">PIN_WaitForThreadTermination</ref>. Only the unique id obtained from a call to <ref refid="group__THREADS_1ga23fe7ae94deab5bf574ff601d3d85a6b" kindref="member">PIN_SpawnInternalThread</ref> can be used for waiting on a thread using <ref refid="group__THREADS_1gaddd0dc2709292f807cb233e5ec0f809a" kindref="member">PIN_WaitForThreadTermination</ref>. if the caller passed nullptr to pThreadUid when creating the thread, then the value returned by this call cannot be used in <ref refid="group__THREADS_1gaddd0dc2709292f807cb233e5ec0f809a" kindref="member">PIN_WaitForThreadTermination</ref>. For application threads or threads created using std::thread()/pthread_create(), the value returned by this function cannot be safely used for any purpose. This function has limited use. It is deprecated and will be removed in future versions of Pin.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="par"><title>Availability:</title><para><bold>Mode:</bold> JIT<linebreak/>
<bold>O/S</bold>: Linux, Windows<linebreak/>
<bold>CPU:</bold> All<linebreak/>
</para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
